#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "how to configure SSL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Unix"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The following command allows to generate a self-signed certificate/key pair:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    $ openssl req -new -newkey rsa:1024 -days 730 -nodes -x509 -keyout server.key -out server.crt\n"
"    Generating a 1024 bit RSA private key\n"
"    ......++++++\n"
"    ...............++++++\n"
"    writing new private key to 'server.key'\n"
"    -----\n"
"    You are about to be asked to enter information that will be incorporated\n"
"    into your certificate request.\n"
"    What you are about to enter is what is called a Distinguished Name or a DN.\n"
"    There are quite a few fields but you can leave some blank\n"
"    For some fields there will be a default value,\n"
"    If you enter '.', the field will be left blank.\n"
"    -----\n"
"    Country Name (2 letter code) [GB]:FR\n"
"    State or Province Name (full name) [Berkshire]:Ile de France\n"
"    Locality Name (eg, city) [Newbury]:Paris\n"
"    Organization Name (eg, company) [My Company Ltd]:\n"
"    Organizational Unit Name (eg, section) []:\n"
"    Common Name (eg, your name or your server's hostname) []:glpi.mycompany.com\n"
"    Email Address []:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"CAUTION: you have to ensure the exact host name in your server URL matches "
"the certificate Common Name attribute. For instance, if your servier URL is "
"http(s)://glpi.mycompany.com/, the common name should be 'glpi.mycompany."
"com'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"This will generate two files, server.key and server.crt. The first one is "
"the server key, and is the private part allowing the server to prove its "
"identity.  The second one is the server certificate, and is the public part "
"allowing other piece of software to check the server identity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "You have to copy those file somewhere in your system configuration:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"     # install -m 600 server.key /etc/pki/tls/private/server.key\n"
"     # install -m 644 server.crt /etc/pki/tls/certs/server.crt\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Then you need to modify Apache configuration, through SSLCertificateFile and "
"SSLCertificateKeyFile directives:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"     # yum install mod_ssl\n"
"     # vi /etc/httpd/conf.d/ssl.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Then you have to restart the server:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "     # service httpd reload\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The certificate can now be used by the agent as certification authority (`--"
"ca-cert-file server.crt`)."
msgstr ""
